Citation.sTitle: Transfer Properties of Glycylglycine from Water to Aqueous NaNO3 CNaClO4 and Na2SO4 Solutions
Citation.sAbstract: Enthalpies of solution and densities of glycylglycine in aqueous solutions of NaNO3, NaClO4, and Na2SO4 were measured at 298.15 K. Standard transfer enthalpies (?trH0), standard transfer partial molar volume (?trV?0), and hydration numbers (Nh) have been determined for glycylglycine. All of the ?trH0 values are negative in the three salt solutions. The relative order of ?trH0 in the same concentration of 1 1 type salts is NaNO3 greater than NaClO4. The ?trH0 in low concentration of Na2SO4 solutions is between the corresponding values in NaNO3 and NaClO4 solutions. With increasing Na2SO4 concentration, the ?trH0 values exceed that in NaNO3 solutions. The ?trV?0 values are positive and vary in the sequence Na2SO4 greater than NaNO3 greater than NaClO4. The results were discussed in terms of various interactions.
